HEADWORD: Sea colander
<hw>Sea" col"an*der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A large
blackfish seaweed (<spn>Agarum Turneri</spn>), the frond of which is
punctured with many little holes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea colewort</ent>⟦br⟧
